definition.value: A carboxylic ester arising from the formal condensation of the alcoholic hydroxy group of one molecule of (3R)-3-hydroxybutanoic acid with the the carboxylic acid group of another. It is a sex pheromone in the European spider Linyphia triangularis.
An organic nitrate salt obtained by reaction of di-mu-iodobis(ethylenediamine)diplatinum(II) with two molar equivalents of nitric acid.
A (13)C-modified compound that is apspartic acid in which the carbon atoms at postions 1 and 4 are present as their (13)C isotopes.

An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from O(3)-{beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-6-O-sulfo-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->6)]-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl}-L-threonine residue.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from O(3)-{beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-6-O-sulfo-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->6)]-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl}-L-serine residue.
A member of the class of benzophenones that is phenol substituted by a 4-fluorobenzoyl group at position 4.
A primary ammonium ion obtained by protonation of the amino goup of any alkylamine; major species at pH 7.3.
Any glycerolipid having an oxidized fatty acyl component.
Any ceramide having an oxidized fatty acyl component.
A composition-only glycan consisting of one 6-deoxyhexosyl group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: dHex1.

A composition-only glycan consisting of six hexosyl groups, six acetaminohexosyl groups, two 6-deoxyhexosyl groups and three N-acetyl-neuraminic acid groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex6 HexNAc6 dHex2 NeuAc3.
A composition-only glycan consisting of two hexosyl groups, three acetaminohexosyl groups and one 6-deoxyhexosyl groups  (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex2 HexNAc3 dHex1.
A composition-only glycan consisting of one hexosyl group, two acetaminohexosyl groups and one sulfate group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex1 HexNAc2 S1.
A D-glucopyranose 6-phosphate where alpha-D-glucose is the sugar component.
A beta-diketone that is tetrahydrocurcumin in which one the methoxy groups has been replaced by a hydrogen atom.
A beta-diketone that is curcumin in which the two methoxy groups have been replaced by hydroxy groups. It is a metabolite of curcumin.
